Additional description of female paratype : The description of the male holotype specimen fits also to the female paratype , with a few additions as follows. The pubescence is partially rubbed off; the cephalic pores are virtually absent and at close inspection only recognizable as a minute, longitudinal, slightly darkened structure, possibly a remnant of part of the pores’ margin; eyes little smaller than in male and hardly vaulted; hind tibiae even shorter and wider than in the male; the gonocoxae were dissected, the diverging tips are of normal shape of
